content:
The legacy Firebase Cloud Messaging API server key is no longer accepted for configuring Android push notifications on mobile connected apps. Because of a change in how Google handles push notifications, Android mobile connected apps now collect the Admin SDK private key and project ID from a Google Firebase project.

To make sure that there’s no disruption to the delivery of your app’s notifications, submit the Firebase Admin SDK private key and project ID required for the new Firebase Cloud Messaging API (HTTP v1).

Get the required information from your Firebase project in the Google Firebase Console. Then submit the information to your mobile connected app’s settings in App Manager.

Configure Android Push Notifications 
FCM features deprecated in June 2023
title: Update Firebase Information for Android Mobile Connected Apps
